idea_implementation: Create or update the file generated_4.sql with this complete content:

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS snapshots_and_blindspots (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    gamedb_id INT REFERENCES games(id),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    player_metrics_count INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK (player_metrics_count > 0) -- Number of active players at this snapshot. e.g., if there are currently five players online in the game instance with id=123456789: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM player_metrics WHERE gamedb_id = 123456789;
    blindspot_count INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK (blindspot_count <= player_metrics_count) -- Number of detected blurred vision or screen issues at this snapshot. e.g., if there are currently two instances where players reported a glitch in the game environment: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM detection WHERE gamedb_id = 123456789 AND type = 'blindspot';
);

This is for opportunity: AI Overlay for Game Development
Make sure the file is complete, working, and production-ready.
